lassic historical problem. Eric Richards reviews the historical debate and examines the methods and sources employed by the combatants past and present. The debates among historians, novelists, politicians and economists are no less passionate today and raise major questions about interpretation and the appropriate frame of reference for the noisy and continuing public debate about the Highland Clearances. This book presents a representative anthology of documents illustrating the historical foundations on which the debate is built. The debate is set in context and the author explains why it is not only important for Scottish patriots but for history in general. Key FeaturesOrganised into two parts; the first considers debates surrounding the Clearances, the second examines a selection of the sources which inform these debatesPresents and analyses an anthology of source material compiled to introduce the debates surrounding the Highland Clearances to audiences learning about historical analysisAsks why passionate debate about the Clearances has been sustained and provides a modern introduction to its main issues  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCroftersxHistoryxScotlandxHighlands. 0aCroftersxHistoryxSourcesxScotlandxHighlands. 0aCrofterszScotlandzHighlandsxHistoryvSources. 0aCrofterszScotlandzHighlandsxHistoryxSources. 0aCrofterszScotlandzHighlandsxHistory. 0aForced migrationxHistoryxScotland. 0aForced migrationxHistoryxSourcesxScotland. 0aForced migrationzScotlandxHistoryvSources. 0aForced migrationzScotlandxHistoryxSources. 0aForced migrationzScotlandxHistory. 0aLand tenurexHistoryxScotlandxHighlands. 0aLand tenurexHistoryxSourcesxScotlandxHighlands. 0aLand tenurezScotlandzHighlandsxHistoryvSources. 0aLand tenurezScotlandzHighlandsxHistoryxSources.